(## 3\) News Authoring \(Step‑by‑Step\)) Tj
T*
(1. Visit the WordPress dashboard:) Tj
T*
(   - **https://beta.investkenya.go.ke/wordpress/wp-admin/**) Tj
T*
(2. Click **Posts** on the left.) Tj
T*
(3. Search for the post: **“News Sample -> duplicate this”**.) Tj
T*
(4. Hover over it and click **Duplicate** \(this creates a clean template copy\).) Tj
T*
(5. Hover over the new duplicate and click **Quick Edit**.) Tj
T*
(6. Fill the **Title**, then copy it and paste it into the **Slug** \(exact same text\).) Tj
T*
(7. If you want tags, update the **Tags** field \(example: `Danger, Critical`\).) Tj
T*
(8. **Do not change anything else.** Click **Update**.) Tj
T*
(9. Hover over the new post again and click **Edit** \(not Elementor\).) Tj
T*
(10. On the right under **Post** you’ll see the **Featured Image**.) Tj
T*
(    - Hover → **Replace**.) Tj
T*
(    - Upload or select from media.) Tj
T*
(11. Scroll down in the editor. You must adjust:) Tj
T*
(    - **Display In Slider:** Yes / No \(controls if it appears in the news slider\).) Tj
T*
(    - **Blog List Image:** select the same image you used as featured image.) Tj
T*
(12. Click **Save Draft** \(top right\).) Tj
T*
(13. Go back to **Posts**, find your draft.) Tj
T*
(14. Hover and click **Edit with Elementor**.) Tj
T*
(15. If the Elementor panel is not visible, click the small icon between **Search** and the **Eye** \(near the Publish button\).) Tj
T*
